<p>This connecting trail strings together three classic Okunikko stops: the rustic Kotoku Onsen, the cascading Yudaki Falls, and the high-elevation hot spring town of Yumoto Onsen. AllTrails describes a moderately rated forest climb that follows the Yukawa River upstream, mixing mossy conifers, wooden bridges, and viewpoints of the turquoise Yuno Lake.</p>

<p>Hikers often combine the route with a soak at either end of the journey. Keep an eye out for geothermal vents steaming beside the boardwalks near Yumoto and enjoy the quiet, uncrowded segments that reveal the park’s volcanic origins.</p>

